Only write the generated app.config if needed (#3009)

* Only write the generated app.config if needed

We compare what we're going to write to what is already there if
present. If the contents are already there, then don't bother.

Note: This is rather naive, as any difference will cause the file to be
written. For example if, for some reason, the order of the binding
redirects changes.

This fixes #3008

* GenerateBindingRedirectsTests code cleanup

* Add unit test

commit_list.message:
Null Ptr Check

In some cases there could be a SECFailure when using nss_cmd but no
actual PR_Error, in that case calling std::str::raw::from_c_str on
PR_ErrorToName(PR_GetError()) could result in a null ptr trying to be
dereferenced. So Split up the command and check for ptr::null().

As a bonus it's probably slightly easier to read.

Implement Bad Cert Callback

Allows you to specify code to run when a SSL certificate fails validation.

Update Makefile

Since I made the tests a separate crate, I had to update the Makefile to
properly handle the dependencies.

Updates for Rust Trunk

many changes
Split command from one line for prettiness

Add Makefile

Update Travis to use the make file.

Also added .gitignore for build artifacts.

Reorganization

Still feeling out crate layouts...

More robust nss database handling

Also initializes RW, fallsback to NoDB Init if needed, creates
directories if possible.

Better concurrency

Avoids a deadlock and is a little more aggressive about protecting NSS
initialization code from being stomped on by concurrent tasks.

change ssl_connect to SSLStream::connect

implemented SSLStream::disconnect

Also updated test to gracefully disconnect

Handle the case where nssdb dir doesn't exist

We'll do a NoDB_Init then.
Allow temporary trusting of certificates from file

Allow nssdb directory to be set, better concurrency

Used the pattern to lock during init from rust-ssl.
This synchronization seems to work better

Added Mutex and moved tests

Multiple tasks trying to access NSS should now properly only init it
once.

Also moved tests to their own module as part of reorg.
Reorganization changes. Removed NSPR calls into it's own library
Appears to be doing SSL communication to some extent
